{
  "texts": [
    "To solve this problem, if the LLM's answer (after minimal cleaning: taking into account the first line only, removing special signs and spaces) does not fall into one of the expected ones, we ask the LLM to produce a new answer until it does.",
    "Non-compliance was practically inexistent for open models, but could rise up to 20% for OpenAI models on \"sensitive\" questions.",
    "For all FA experiments, we used a temperature of 0.7, as in (Argyle et al., 2023).",
    "In next-token-probability (NTP), that was used for the results presented in the main text of this article, we ask the LLM to produce just one token for each distinct profile in the WVS data, directly yielding a probability distribution over the valid answers.",
    "In this strategy, the valid available answers are coded as single tokens, e.g."
  ]
}